        <h2 id="salad">Salad</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 2-3 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 1</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Cucumbers</td>
                    <td>2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Tomatoes</td>
                    <td>2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Lettuce</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>1 spoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Oil</td>
                    <td>1-2 tbsp</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong>  Wash the cucumber, tomatoes, and lettuce.<br>
<strong>Step 2:</strong> Cut the cucumber into small pieces.<br>
<strong>Step 3:</strong> Cut the tomatoes into small pieces.<br>
<strong>Step 4:</strong> Tear the lettuce into pieces.<br>
<strong>Step 5:</strong>Put all ingredients into a bowl.<br>
<strong>Step 6:</strong> Add salt.<br>
<strong>Step 7:</strong>Add oil (1 or 2 spoons).<br>
<strong>Step 8:</strong>Mix everything well.<br>
<strong>Step 9:</strong> Serve the salad.
</p>


<h2 id="eggs">Scrambled eggs</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 5-6 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 1</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>1 pinch</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Oil</td>
                    <td>1 tbsp</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Crack 2 eggs into a bowl.<br>
<strong>Step 2:</strong> Add a pinch of salt.<br>
<strong>Step 3:</strong> Mix the eggs with a fork.<br>
<strong>Step 4:</strong> Heat a pan.<br>
<strong>Step 5:</strong> Add a little oil or butter to the pan.<br>
<strong>Step 6:</strong> Pour the eggs into the pan.<br>
<strong>Step 7:</strong> Stir gently while cooking.<br>
<strong>Step 8:</strong> Cook for 2 or 3 minutes.<br>
<strong>Step 9:</strong> Turn off the heat and serve.
</p>

<h2 id="sandwich">Sandwich</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 3 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 1</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Bread </td>
                    <td>2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Cheese</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Ham</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Butter</td>
                    <td>1 tsb</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong>  Take 2 slices of bread.<br>
<strong>Step 2:</strong> Spread butter on the bread.<br>
<strong>Step 3:</strong> Put cheese on one slice..<br>
<strong>Step 4:</strong> Put ham on top of the cheese.<br>
<strong>Step 5:</strong> Cover with the second slice of bread.<br>
<strong>Step 6:</strong> Serve and eat.<br></p>


